Detectives have concluded the verification of a consignment seized at the Mombasa port on Tuesday and recovered 334 pieces of elephant tusks with estimate value of Sh197 million.The elephant tusks were discovered in two evergreen containers that were destined for CambodiaKRA head of investigations David Yegoh said that they have a list of suspects that police are following.Read: [VIDEO] Elephant tusks disguised as logs seized in MombasaLast week, a man who had been found with two worth Sh1.8 million was sentenced to five years in jail or pay a fine of Sh1 million.Geoffrey Njogu was sentenced on Thursday by Kibera principal magistrate Benard Ochoi, two years after he was found with the tusks.Read: Man found with elephant tusks to spend five years in jail or pay Sh1 million fine